Executive Profile
Anthony J. Topazi  Chief Executive Officer of Mississippi Power and President of Mississippi Power, Cooperative EnergyAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships67--
Background

		Mr. Anthony J. Topazi has been the President and Chief Executive Officer of South Mississippi Electric Power Association since January 1, 2004. Mr. Topazi served as the Chief Operating Officer and Executive Vice President of Southern Company from August 13, 2010 to July 1, 2012. He served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of Mississippi Power Co. from January 1, 2004 to August 13, 2010. In this role, he also served as the primary executive responsible for ... the business development and government approval of the first Transport Integrated Gasification (TRIG) plant to be built in the Southern Company system. He served as an Executive Vice President of Southern Company Generation and Energy Marketing at Southern Company Services Inc. from November 2000 to December 2003. Mr. Topazi served as an Senior Vice President of Southern Power Company from November 2002 to December 2003. He served as Vice President of Southern Power Company from March 2001 to November 2002 and served as its Executive Officer. He served as Vice President of Southern Company Services, Inc. from December 1999 to December 2003 and as Vice President of Alabama Power Company from March 1991 to December 1999. He began his Alabama Power career as a cooperative education student engineer and rose to numerous executive positions in its Birmingham and Western divisions. As chair of the Tuscaloosa County, AL, Industrial Development Authority, he assumed a primary role in recruiting to Alabama the first Mercedes-Benz automotive assembly plant outside Germany. Mr. Topazi served as the Director of New Orleans Branch of Federal Reserve Bank of Atlanta. He serves as a Director of Whitney Bank. He served as Director of Southern Power Company. He serves as Director of Mast, Inc., and the Gulf Coast Community Foundation and on the Nature Conservancy of Mississippi board of trustees. He served as an Independent Director of Hancock Holding Company since January 25, 2007 until April 21, 2016. He served as a Director Hancock Bank since 2004. He served as a Director of Mississippi Power Co from January 1, 2004 to August 13, 2010. He is a Member of the de Toqueville Society of United Way of America. He chairs the Infrastructure Committee of the Governor's Commission on Recovery, Rebuilding and Renewal; Momentum Mississippi and the Gulf Coast Business Council. He served on the Blueprint Mississippi steering committee and co-chaired the economic development work team. Mr. Topazi serves on Mississippi Economic Council Board of Directors as Vice Chair of Mississippi Partnership for Economic Development and as chair-elect of Mississippi Gulf Coast Chamber of Commerce. He holds Bachelor's Degree in Electrical Engineering from Auburn University.Read Full Background




